      name_rus: 'Местная кухня',
      name_bel: 'Мясцовая кухня',
      info_eng: 'Every Arab country cooks couscous in its own way. They are always based on the same name cereal, vegetables, meat (lamb, chicken, sometimes beef, and sometimes all at once). The vegetables are cooked in broth with the bone in it and cut coarsely so that they don\'t lose their shape. Groats are traditionally steamed in special couscous pots - hence the unique taste. Vegetarians in Morocco can try a vegetable version of the dish. The most popular type of Moroccan couscous is couscous au sept légumes (with seven vegetables).',
